      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is needed because the actual tick clock (timer B) is derived from AHB clock, then when the bus frequency is decreased the tick is delayed. \n\nThis patch uses a fixed external clock, i suppose it is 12 MHz but not sure (i.e. it could be 24 MHz / 2), anyways the UNKNOWN bit is used by emCORE loader to configure the USEC_TIMER (timer E) so it is safe to use it. \n\nIn addition the new resulting frequency for timer B is more precise (10000 Hz vs 10015 Hz).",
